

Compling for Linux/Unix/Mac platform:
	adapt Makefile with the correct directory in the section "userspecified variables"
	and run 
    make 
    
    Usse the file "sload" for loading 

Compiling for Windows 
	Compilation on the windows platform has not been tested yet.  
	I used a cross-compiler on Linux for compiling the windows executable. 
	Set setup mingw-cross-env and wine on some Linux machine, 
	Copy the Mathlink developer files 
		e.g. C:\Program Files\Wolfram Research\Mathematica\7.0\SystemFiles\Links\MathLink\DeveloperKit\Windows*
	from Windows to the linux computer (copyied them into the corresponding Mathematica directory on linux)
		e.g. /usr/local/Wolfram/gridMathematicaServer/7.0/SystemFiles/Links/MathLink/DeveloperKit/
	Adapt the user-defined variables in Makefile.win32
	and run 

    make win32


